THE EUROPEAN ECONOMIC COMMUNITY

THE SWITZERLAND PROPERTY

WISHING , on the occasion of the enlargement of the European Economic Community , to consolidate and extend economic relations between the Community and Switzerland and to ensure the harmonious development of their trade , while respecting fair conditions of competition , with a view to contributing to the construction of Europe ;
DECIDED to this end , in accordance with the provisions of the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade on the establishment of free trade areas , the progressive removal of barriers to their entire trade .
RECOGNISE to consider , taking into account all elements of the assessment , in particular the development of the Community , the possibility of strengthening and deepening its relations if their extension to areas not covered by this Agreement should prove useful in the interest of their economies ;
HAVE DECIDED , in order to achieve these objectives and whereas no provision of this Agreement may be interpreted as relieving the Parties of their obligations under other international treaties ,
TO CONCLUDE THIS AGREEMENT :

The purpose of this Agreement is to :
( a ) promote the harmonious development of their economic relations through the expansion of trade in goods between the European Economic Community and the Swiss Confederation , thereby fostering the development of economic activity in the Community and in Switzerland , improving living and employment conditions , increasing productivity and financial stability ;
( b ) ensure fair conditions of competition in the trade in goods between the Parties ;
( c ) thus contribute to the harmonious development and expansion of world trade by removing barriers to trade .

This Agreement shall apply to products originating in the Community and Switzerland ,
