Article 18
The Contracting Parties shall not apply measures or practices of an internal tax nature which , directly or indirectly , discriminate against products of one Contracting Party and products of equivalent origin of the other Contracting Party .
Goods exported to the territory of a Contracting Party may not be reimbursed for domestic duties higher than those levied directly or indirectly on such goods .
Article 19
Payments relating to the movement of goods and the transfer of these amounts to the Member State of the Community where the creditor is domiciled or to Switzerland are not subject to restrictions .
The Contracting Parties shall not apply foreign exchange restrictions or administrative restrictions on the granting , repayment and acceptance of short- and medium @-@ term credits in connection with commercial transactions in which a resident is involved .
Article 20
This Agreement does not preclude import , export or transit bans or restrictions justified on grounds of public morality , order and safety , the protection of the health and life of human beings , animals or plants , national cultural heritage of artistic , historical or archaeological value or industrial and commercial property , nor does it preclude regulations on gold and silver .
However , these prohibitions or restrictions must not constitute a means of arbitrary discrimination or a disguised restriction on trade between the contracting parties .
Article 21
This Agreement shall in no way prevent a Contracting Party from taking measures :
( a ) which it considers necessary in order to prevent disclosure of information contrary to its essential security interests ;
( b ) concerning trade in arms , munitions and war material or research , development or production indispensable for defence purposes , provided that such measures do not adversely affect the conditions of competition with regard to products not intended specifically for military purposes ;
( c ) which it considers essential for its own security in times of war or in the event of serious international tensions .
Article 22
1 . The Contracting Parties shall refrain from any measure likely to jeopardize the achievement of the objectives of this Agreement .
2 . They shall take all appropriate measures of a general or special nature to fulfil their obligations under this Agreement .
If one Party considers that the other Party has not fulfilled an obligation under this Agreement , it may take appropriate measures in accordance with the conditions and procedures laid down in Article 27 .
Article 23
1 . Insofar as they are liable to affect trade in goods between the Community and Switzerland , they are incompatible with the proper functioning of this Agreement ;
( i ) all agreements between undertakings , decisions of associations of undertakings and concerted practices between undertakings which have as their object or effect the prevention , restriction or distortion of competition in terms of production and movement of goods ;
( ii ) abuse of a dominant position by one or more undertakings in all or a substantial part of the territory of the Parties ;
( iii ) any State aid which distorts or threatens to distort competition by favouring certain undertakings or sectors of production .
2 . Where a Contracting Party considers that a practice is incompatible with this Article , it may take appropriate measures in accordance with the conditions and procedures laid down in Article 27 .

If the increase in imports of a particular product seriously damages or threatens to damage a branch of production in the territory of a Contracting Party and if the increase is attributable to :
- to the reduction or elimination of customs duties and charges having equivalent effect on such goods in the territory of the importing Contracting Party provided for in this Agreement ;
- and to the fact that the duties and charges levied by the exporting Contracting Party on imports of raw materials or intermediate products used in the manufacture of the goods in question are substantially lower than the corresponding duties and charges levied by the importing Contracting Party ,
the Contracting Party concerned may take appropriate measures in accordance with the conditions and procedures laid down in Article 27 .

Where a Contracting Party establishes dumping practices in its relations with the other Contracting Party , it may take appropriate measures against such practices in accordance with the conditions and procedures laid down in Article 27 , in accordance with the provisions of the Agreement implementing Article VI of the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade .
Article 26
In the event of serious disturbances in an economic activity or difficulties which may lead to a serious regional deterioration of the economic situation , the Contracting Party concerned may take appropriate measures in accordance with the conditions and procedures laid down in Article 27 .

1 . If a Contracting Party establishes an administrative procedure for the import of goods which may cause the difficulties referred to in Articles 24 and 26 in order to obtain rapid information on the development of trade flows , it shall inform the other Contracting Party accordingly .
2 . In the cases referred to in Articles 22 to 26 , before taking the measures provided for therein , and in the cases referred to in paragraph 3 ( d ) , the Contracting Party concerned shall provide the Joint Committee with all the relevant information as soon as possible in order to enable a thorough examination of the situation with a view to finding a solution acceptable to the Contracting Parties .
Priority must be given to those measures which have the least impact on the functioning of this Agreement .
The safeguard measures will be notified immediately to the Joint Committee and will be the subject of regular consultations , in particular with a view to their abolition as soon as possible .
( 3 ) The following shall apply to the implementation of paragraph 2 :
( a ) As regards Article 23 , any Contracting Party may refer the matter to the Joint Committee if it considers that a particular practice is incompatible with the good functioning of that Agreement within the meaning of Article 23 ( 1 ) .
In order to examine the case and , where appropriate , to remedy the practice in question , the Parties shall provide the Joint Committee with all relevant information and the necessary assistance .
If the Contracting Party concerned does not put an end to the practices complained of within the period laid down in the Joint Committee , or if agreement is not reached within three months of referral to the Joint Committee , the Contracting Party concerned may take the safeguard measures it deems necessary to remedy the serious difficulties arising from such practices , in particular by withdrawing tariff concessions .
( b ) With regard to Article 24 , the difficulties arising from the situation described therein shall be notified to the Joint Committee for consideration , which may take any appropriate decisions to remedy them .
If the Mixed Committee or the implementing Contracting Party has not taken a decision to remedy the difficulties within thirty days of notification , the importing Contracting Party shall be entitled to impose a compensation levy on the imported goods .
In calculating this countervailing levy , the incidence of customs disparities found for the processed raw materials or intermediates shall be taken into account in relation to the value of the product concerned .
( c ) Consultation on Article 25 shall take place in the Joint Committee before appropriate action is taken by the Contracting Party concerned .
( d ) If exceptional circumstances necessitating immediate intervention preclude prior examination , the Contracting Party concerned may take without delay the necessary safeguards to remedy the situation referred to in Articles 24 , 25 and 26 , as well as in the case of export subsidies having a direct and immediate effect on the movement of goods .

The Contracting Party concerned may take the necessary protective measures in the event of payment difficulties which have already occurred or are seriously threatened by one or more Member States of the Community or Switzerland .
