Article 30
1 . The Mixed Committee shall consist of representatives of the Community , on the one hand , and representatives of Switzerland , on the other .
( 2 ) The Mixed Committee shall speak by mutual agreement .
Article 31
1 . The Joint Committee shall be chaired alternately by the Contracting Parties in accordance with the Rules of Procedure of the Committee .
2 . The Mixed Committee shall meet at least once a year at the instigation of its President to examine the general functioning of this Agreement .
It shall also meet at the request of a contracting party as often as is necessary in accordance with its rules of procedure .
3 . The Mixed Committee may decide to set up working groups to assist it in the performance of its tasks .
Article 32
1 . If a Contracting Party considers that extending the relations established by this Agreement to areas not covered by this Agreement would be beneficial in the interests of the economies of both Parties , it shall submit a reasoned request to the other Contracting Party .
The Parties may delegate to the Joint Committee the examination of this request and , where appropriate , the preparation of recommendations , in particular with regard to the opening of negotiations .
2 . The agreements resulting from the negotiations referred to in paragraph 1 shall be subject to ratification or approval by the Parties in accordance with their own procedures .
Article 33
The Annexes and Protocols annexed to this Agreement form an integral part of the Agreement .
Article 34
Any Contracting Party may terminate this Agreement by notifying the other Contracting Party .
This Agreement shall expire twelve months after the date of such notification .
Article 35
This Agreement shall apply to the territories in which the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community is applicable in accordance with that Treaty , on the one hand , and to the territory of the Swiss Confederation , on the other .
Article 36
This Agreement is drawn up in two original texts , each in Danish , English , French , German , Italian , Dutch and Norwegian , each text being equally authentic .
This Agreement shall be subject to the consent of the Parties in accordance with their own procedures .
It shall enter into force on 1 January 1973 , provided that the parties have notified each other of the completion of the necessary procedures before that date .
If such notification is made after that date , this Agreement shall enter into force on the first day of the second month following the notification .
The latest date for notification is 30 November 1973 .
The provisions applicable as from 1 April 1973 shall enter into force simultaneously with this Agreement if the Agreement enters into force after that date .
