EUROPEAN CONVENTION ON THE EXCHANGE OF REAGENCIES FOR TYPING
THE MEMBER STATES OF THE EUROPAIN which have signed this Convention ,
The reagents for tissue typing are only available in limited quantities .
It is highly desirable for the Member States to support each other , if necessary , in the procurement of such reagents in a spirit of European solidarity .
This mutual assistance is only possible if the nature and use of these reagents for tissue typing are subject to rules jointly established by the Member States and if the necessary facilities and exemptions are granted for the import of these reagents ;
HOW TO CONVENT :

( 1 ) For the purposes of this Convention , the term &quot; tissue typing reagents &quot; refers to all reagents of human , Turkish , vegetable and other origin used for tissue typing .
( 2 ) The provisions of Articles 2 to 6 of this Convention shall also apply to cells of known antigenic composition used in the study of the reagents in question .

The Contracting Parties undertake to transfer reagents for tissue typification to other Contracting Parties who need them , in return for reimbursement of the costs of their extraction , preparation and transport and , where appropriate , their purchase price , provided that they themselves have sufficient supplies for their own needs .

Tissue typing reagents will be made available to other Contracting Parties only on condition that there is no profit to be made from them , that they are only used for medical and scientific purposes , i.e. not for commercial purposes , and only supplied to laboratories designated by the participating Governments in accordance with Article 6 of this Convention .

1 . The Contracting Parties shall ensure compliance with the provisions of the Protocol to this Convention .
( 2 ) They shall also observe the relevant international standard provisions adopted by them .
( 3 ) Each shipment of reagents for tissue typing shall be accompanied by a certificate that they have been manufactured in accordance with the provisions of the Protocol .
