TRADE INTERNATIONAL CONVENTION WITH CARNETS TIR ( TIR- CONVENTION )
THE CONTRACT PARTIES -
WISHING to facilitate the international transport of goods by road ,
CONSIDERING that the improvement of transport conditions is an essential factor in the development of cooperation between them ,
SUPPORTING simplification and harmonisation of administrative arrangements in international transport , in particular at borders ;
ARE AGREED as follows :
CHAPTER I GENERAL
a ) Definitions

For the purposes of this Convention , the term ( a ) &quot; TIR- transport &quot; means the transport of goods from a customs point of departure to a customs point of destination under the so @-@ called &quot; TIR- procedure &quot; laid down in this Convention ;
( b ) &quot; import and exit taxes &quot; shall mean customs duties and all other charges , taxes , charges and other charges levied on the occasion of or in connection with the import or export of goods , without the fees and charges which are approximately limited in amount to the cost of the services provided ;
( c ) &quot; Road vehicles &quot; not only road vehicles but also all trailers and semi @-@ trailers intended to be towed by such vehicles ;
( d ) &quot; lorries &quot; of interconnected vehicles used as a unit in road transport ;
( e ) &quot; container &quot; means transport equipment ( furniture transport container , removable tank or other similar equipment ) which ( i ) constitutes a hollow body wholly or partially closed for receiving goods ;
( ii ) is durable and therefore resistant enough to be reused ;
( iii ) is specifically designed to facilitate the transport of goods by one or more means of transport without transshipment of contents ;
( iv ) is designed to be easy to handle , in particular when transferring from one mode of transport to another ;
( v ) is designed to be easily loaded and unloaded , and
vi ) has a volume of at least one cubic metre ;
&quot; detachable bodies &quot; are considered containers ;
f ) &quot; Departure Customs Office &quot; is the customs office of a Contracting Party at which the international transport begins in the TIR- procedure for the total or partial cargo ;
g ) &quot; Customs office of destination &quot; is the customs office of a Contracting Party at which the international transport ends in the TIR- procedure for the total or partial cargo ;
h ) &quot; Transit Customs Office &quot; is the customs office of a Contracting Party through which a road vehicle , lorry or container is imported or exported as part of a TIR- transport ;
j ) &quot; Persons &quot; both natural and legal persons ;
( k ) &quot; exceptionally heavy or bulky goods &quot; any heavy or bulky objects which , due to their weight , dimensions or nature , are not normally transported in a closed road vehicle or container ;
l ) &quot; guarantor association &quot; means an association authorised by the customs authorities of a Contracting Party to guarantee the users of the TIR- procedure .
( b ) Scope

This Convention shall apply to the transport of goods in which the goods are transported without transhipment across one or more frontiers from a customs outpost of one Contracting Party to a customs point of destination of another or the same Contracting Party in road vehicles , trucks or containers , provided that part of the route between the beginning and the end of the TIR- transport is carried out by road .

( a ) the transport of goods shall be carried out ( i ) by road vehicles , freight trains or containers previously approved under the conditions laid down in Chapter III ( a ) ; or
( ii ) with other road vehicles , trucks or containers , provided that the conditions laid down in Chapter III , paragraph ( c ) are respected ;
( b ) that the transport of goods shall be guaranteed by associations authorised under Article 6 and that the transport shall be carried out using a TIR carnet corresponding to the model set out in Annex 1 .
c ) Basic Provisions

For goods transported under the TIR- procedure , no payment or deposit of entry or exit taxes is required at the transit customs offices .
Article 5
( 1 ) Goods which are transported by road vehicles , freight trains or containers in the TIR- procedure under customs closure shall in principle not be inspected at the transit customs offices .
( 2 ) However , in order to prevent abuses , customs authorities may , in exceptional cases and in particular where there is suspicion of irregularity , inspect the goods at the transit customs offices .
CHAPTER II DISTRIBUTION OF CARNETS TIR LIABILITY OF CITIZENS CONNECTIONS

( 1 ) Each Contracting Party may , against collateral and under conditions specified by the Contracting Party , grant authorisation to associations to issue TIR Carnets , either themselves or through their associated associations , and to assume the surety .
( 2 ) An association shall be admitted in a country only if its guarantee also extends to the liabilities arising in that country from the transport of goods by TIR Carnets issued by foreign associations belonging to the same international organisation as the guarantor association .

Carnet @-@ TIR- Forms sent to the guarantor associations by the foreign associations associated with them or by international organizations , are exempt from entry and exit taxes , import and export bans and import and export restrictions .
Article 8
( 1 ) The guarantor association shall undertake to pay the due entry or exit fees plus any default interest payable in accordance with the customs laws and other customs regulations of the country in which an irregularity has been detected in connection with a TIR- transport .
The guarantor association is jointly and severally liable with the persons who owe the aforementioned amounts for the payment of these amounts .
( 2 ) If the laws and other provisions of a Contracting Party do not provide for the payment of the entry or exit dues in the cases referred to in paragraph 1 , the guarantor association shall undertake to pay , under the same conditions , an amount equal to the entry or exit dues plus any default interest .
( 3 ) Each Contracting Party shall determine the maximum amount which , in accordance with paragraphs 1 and 2 , may be claimed from the guarantor association for each TIR carnet .
( 4 ) The liability of the guarantor association vis @-@ à @-@ vis the authorities of the country in which the departure customs office is located commences when the TIR carnet has been accepted by the customs office .
In the other countries through which the goods are still transported under the TIR- procedure , liability begins with the import of the goods or with the receipt of the TIR carnet by the customs office , at which the TIR- transport is resumed if it has been suspended pursuant to Article 26 ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) .
( 5 ) The liability of the guarantor association shall not only extend to the goods specified in the TIR carnet , but also to goods which are not specified in the TIR carnet , but which are in part of the vehicle or container under customs clearance ; it shall not extend to other goods .
( 6 ) The information contained in the TIR carnet on the Goods shall be deemed to be correct in determining the charges referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 until proven otherwise .
7 . When the amounts referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 are due , the competent authorities shall , as far as possible , require the person or persons who directly owe them to pay them before inviting the guarantor association to pay such amounts .

( 1 ) The guarantor association determines the validity period of the TIR Carnet and determines the last day of validity after which the carnet can no longer be presented to the customs office for acceptance .
( 2 ) If the carnet has been accepted by the customs office of departure at the latest by the last day of validity pursuant to paragraph 1 , it shall remain valid at the customs office of destination until the end of the TIR- transport .

( 1 ) The TIR Carnet may be carried out under reservation or without reservation ; a reservation must relate to facts concerning the TIR- transport itself .
These facts must be stated on the TIR carnet .
( 2 ) If the customs authorities of a country have carried out a TIR Carnet without reservation , they may no longer require the guarantor association to pay the amounts referred to in Article 8 ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) , unless the registration certificate has been obtained improperly or fraudulently .
Article 11
( 1 ) If a TIR Carnet has not been completed or under reservation , the competent authorities may require the guarantor association to pay the amounts referred to in Article 8 paragraphs 1 and 2 only if they have notified the guarantor association in writing of the non @-@ completion or completion of the TIR Carnet within one year of the acceptance of the TIR Carnet by the customs authorities .
The same applies if the registration certificate has been obtained improperly or fraudulently , but in these cases the period is two years .
2 . The request for payment of the amounts referred to in Article 8 , paragraphs 1 and 2 , shall be addressed to the guarantor association not earlier than three months and not later than two years after the date of notification to the association that the carnet has not been carried out or only conditionally , or that the registration certificate has been obtained improperly or fraudulently .
However , if the matter has been the subject of judicial proceedings within the abovementioned period of two years , the request for payment must be made within one year of the date on which the court decision has become final .
( 3 ) The guarantor association shall pay the required amounts within three months of the date of the request for payment .
The amounts paid shall be reimbursed to the guarantor if , within two years from the date of the requests for payment , satisfactory proof has been provided to the customs authorities that there was no irregularity in the transport in question .
CHAPTER III ARTICLE TRANSPORT WITH TIR CARNETS
a ) Approval of vehicles and containers
Article 12
Sections ( a ) and ( b ) shall only apply if each road vehicle in terms of design and equipment complies with the conditions laid down in Annex 2 and has been registered in accordance with the procedure laid down in Annex 3 .
The seal recognition certificate ( registration certificate ) must correspond to the sample of Annex 4 .
Article 13
( 1 ) Sections ( a ) and ( b ) of this Chapter shall apply only if the containers have been constructed in accordance with the conditions laid down in Annex 7 , Part I , and have been approved in accordance with the procedure laid down in Part II of that Annex .
( 2 ) In the case of containers authorised to be transported under closed customs conditions in accordance with the Customs Convention on Containers 1956 , the related United Nations Conventions , the Customs Convention on Containers of 1972 or any international Conventions replacing or amending this Convention , they shall be deemed to comply with the provisions of paragraph 1 and shall be recognised without re @-@ authorisation for transport under the TIR- procedure .
Article 14
( 1 ) Each Contracting Party reserves the right not to recognise as valid the registration of road vehicles or containers which do not comply with the provisions of Articles 12 and 13 .
However , the contracting parties will avoid delays in carriage if the deficiencies identified are minor and there is no risk of smuggling .
( 2 ) Road vehicles or containers which no longer comply with the conditions governing their registration may not be re @-@ used for the transport of goods under customs clearance until their original condition has been restored or the vehicle or containers have been re @-@ registered .
b ) Carrying out transport with TIR carnets
Article 15
( 1 ) No special customs document is required for the temporary import of road vehicles , trucks or containers used for the transport of goods in the TIR- procedure .
A safety deposit is not required for road vehicles , trucks or containers .
( 2 ) Paragraph 1 shall not prevent a Contracting Party from requiring the designated customs office to undertake the formalities provided for by national law in order to ensure that the road vehicle , lorry or container is re @-@ exported after completion of the TIR- transport .
Article 16
Road vehicles or trucks carrying out TIR- transport shall bear a rectangular plaque in front and rear , corresponding to the characteristics of Annex 5 , with the inscription &quot; TIR . &quot;
These panels must be placed in such a way that they are clearly visible ; they must be removable .
Article 17
( 1 ) A separate TIR carnet must be issued for each road vehicle or container .
However , a single carnet can be produced for one truck or for several containers loaded on a single road vehicle or truck .
In such a case , the goods manifest of the TIR Carnet must specify the contents of each vehicle or container belonging to a lorry separately .
( 2 ) The TIR Carnet is only valid for one journey .
It must contain at least as many separable acceptance and completion sections as are required for the transport in question .
Article 18
A TIR- transport may be carried out via several departure and destination customs offices ; unless otherwise agreed by the Contracting Party or the Contracting Parties concerned , a ) the departure customs offices must be located in the same country ;
b ) destination customs offices may not be located in more than two different countries ;
c ) the total number of points of departure and destination shall not exceed four .
Article 19
The goods and the road vehicle , the truck or the container must be presented to the point of departure with the TIR carnet .
The customs authorities of the country of origin shall take the necessary measures to verify the correctness of the goods manifest and to set up the customs closures or to examine the customs closures set up by persons authorised to do so under their responsibility .
Article 20
Customs authorities may set a time limit for the passage through their country and require the road vehicle , lorry or container to comply with a prescribed route .
Article 21
The road vehicle , the truck or the container must be presented for inspection with the cargo and the associated TIR carnet of each transit customs post and the destination customs post .
Article 22
1 . The transit customs offices of each Contracting Party shall , as a rule , recognise the intact customs closures imposed by the customs authorities of the other Contracting Parties , unless the goods are inspected in accordance with Article 5 , paragraph 2 .
Customs authorities may , however , add their own customs closures if this is necessary for control .
2 . Customs closures so recognised by a Contracting Party shall enjoy the same legal protection in their territory as national customs closures .
Article 23
Customs authorities may only accompany road vehicles , trucks or containers in their country at the carrier &apos;s expense in exceptional cases ,
- to inspect and inspect the load of road vehicles , trucks or containers on the way .

If the customs authorities carry out an inspection of the cargo of a road vehicle , a lorry or a container at a transit customs post or on the way , they will have to record the new customs closures and the type of checks carried out on the Carnet TIRsections used in their country on the corresponding master sheets and on the sections remaining in the TIR carnet .

If customs closures are violated on the way in cases other than those referred to in Articles 24 and 35 , or if goods are destroyed or damaged without violation of customs closures , the TIR procedure and protocol contained in the TIR carnet will be incorporated in accordance with the instructions for the use of the TIR carnet contained in Annex 1 , without prejudice to national legislation .
Article 26
( 1 ) If a transport by TIR Carnet on a section touches the territory of a State which is not a Party to this Convention , TIR- transport shall be suspended during transit through that territory .
In such a case , the customs authorities of the Contracting Party through whose territory the goods are subsequently transported shall recognise the TIR carnet for the continuation of the TIR- transport , provided that the customs closures and / or the nameplates remain intact .
( 2 ) The same shall apply to the part of the route on which the TIR carnet holder does not use the carnet in the territory of a Contracting Party because simpler procedures for transporting customs goods are available or the use of such a procedure is not necessary .
( 3 ) In such cases , the customs offices at which the TIR- transport is suspended or resumed shall be considered as transit customs office at the exit or transit customs office at the entrance .

Subject to the provisions of this Convention , in particular Article 18 thereof , the designated Customs Body may be replaced by another designated Customs Body .

Upon arrival of the cargo at the destination customs office , the TIR carnet shall be processed without delay , provided that the goods are supplied to another customs procedure or cleared for free circulation .
c ) Provisions for the transport of exceptionally heavy or bulky goods
Article 29
( 1 ) This section shall apply only to the transport of exceptionally heavy or bulky goods referred to in point ( k ) of Article 1 .
( 2 ) When using this section , unusually heavy and bulky goods may be transported by vehicles or containers without a customs seal , depending on the decision of the outgoing customs office .
( 3 ) This paragraph shall be applied only if , in the opinion of the outgoing customs office , the identity of the exceptionally heavy or bulky goods and the accessories , if any , carried with them can be readily recorded on the basis of an existing description , or if such goods can be marked with customs seals or identification marks , so that they cannot be replaced or removed without leaving clear traces .
Article 30
All provisions of this Convention , which do not derogate from the specific provisions of this Section , shall also apply to the transport of exceptionally heavy or bulky goods by TIR- procedure .
Article 31
The liability of the guarantor association extends not only to the goods listed in the TIR carnet , but also to goods which are not listed in the TIR carnet , but which are located on the loading area or between the goods listed in the TIR carnet .
Article 32
The TIR carnet used must be marked &quot; Unusually heavy or bulky goods &quot; on the envelope and in all sections in English or French in highlighted letters .
Article 33
The customs office of departure may require that cargo lists , photographs , plans , etc . , which are necessary for securing the identity of the goods transported , be attached to the TIR carnet .
In this case , it stamps these papers , attaches a copy to the back of the Carnet @-@ TIR- cover sheet and notes this in all commodity manifestos .
Article 34
The transit customs offices of each Contracting Party shall recognise the customs closures and / or nameplates affixed by the competent authorities of the other Contracting Parties .
They may , however , additionally affix custom closures and / or nameplates , but must note the newly affixed custom closures and / or nameplates on the Carnet TIRsections used in their country , on the corresponding master sheets and on the sections remaining in the TIR carnet .
Article 35
If customs authorities are required to remove custom seals or nameplates at a transit customs post or on the way for inspection of the cargo , they shall indicate the newly attached custom seals and / or nameplates on the sections of the Carnet TIRs used in their country , on the corresponding master sheets and on the sections remaining in the TIR carnet .
CHAPTER IV Irregularities
Article 36
Anyone who infringes the provisions of this Convention shall be liable to prosecution under the laws of the country in which the infringement was committed .
Article 37
If it cannot be established where the irregularity was committed , it shall be deemed to have been committed in the territory of the Contracting Party in which it was established .
Article 38
( 1 ) Each Contracting Party shall be entitled to temporarily or permanently exclude from the facilitation of this Convention a person who is guilty of a serious infringement of the customs laws or other customs regulations applicable to the international transport of goods .
( 2 ) This exclusion shall be communicated immediately to the customs authorities of the Contracting Party in whose territory the person concerned is domiciled or has his / her place of business and to the guarantor ( s ) of the country in which the infringement has been committed .
Article 39
1 . The contracting parties shall not take into account minor deviations in the fulfilment of obligations related to the time limit and the route .

Furthermore , discrepancies between the information contained in the TIR Carnet Manifesto and the contents of the road vehicle , lorry or container shall not be regarded as infringements by the holder of Carnet TIRs within the meaning of this Convention if satisfactory proof is provided to the competent authorities that these discrepancies are not due to errors committed knowingly or negligently in the loading or shipment of the goods or in the completion of the TIR Carnet Manifesto .
Article 40
The customs administrations of the country of origin and destination shall not charge the Carnet TIRholder for any discrepancies found there , if these discrepancies concern customs procedures which took place before or after the TIR- transport and in which the Carnet holder was not involved .
Article 41
If satisfactory proof has been furnished to the customs authorities that the goods listed in the goods manifest of a TIR Carnet have been lost or irretrievably lost by accident or force majeure , or that they are missing due to natural loss due to their nature , exemption from the customary duties and duties shall be granted .
Article 42
Upon a reasoned request by a Contracting Party , the competent authorities of the Contracting Parties affected by a TIR- transport shall provide it with all available information necessary for the application of Articles 39 , 40 and 41 .
CHAPTER V EXPLANATIONS
Article 43
The explanatory notes in Annex 6 and Annex 7 , Part III , contain interpretations of certain provisions of this Convention and its annexes .
They also reflect some recommended practices .
CHAPTER VI VARIOUS

Each Contracting Party shall grant the participating guarantor associations facilities for the transfer of the necessary means of payment ( a ) for the payment of the amounts requested by the authorities of the Contracting Parties pursuant to Article 8 ; and
b ) to pay for the Carnet TIRforms sent to the guarantor associations by foreign associations associated with them or by international organizations .
Article 45
Each Contracting Party shall publish a list of departure customs offices , transit customs offices and destination customs offices authorised to carry out TIR- transports .
Neighbouring contracting parties agree by mutual agreement on the appropriate border customs posts and their opening hours .
Article 46
( 1 ) No charges shall be levied for customs official acts provided for in this Convention , unless such acts take place outside the days , hours or places normally provided for therefor .
( 2 ) The Contracting Parties shall , as far as possible , facilitate customs clearance of perishable goods at customs offices .
Article 47
1 . This Convention shall not exclude any restrictions or controls laid down in national legislation on grounds of public morality , public safety , hygiene or public health , veterinary or phytosanitary measures , or the levying of charges to be imposed under these provisions .
( 2 ) This Convention shall not preclude the application of other national provisions on transport .
Article 48
This Convention does not preclude the adoption by Contracting Parties forming a customs or economic union of special provisions for the transport of goods which begin , end or transit through their territories , provided that these provisions do not restrict the facilitation provided for in this Convention .

This Convention does not preclude the application of further facilities granted by the Parties either unilaterally or under two or more bilateral agreements , provided that such facilities do not impede the application of this Convention and , in particular , the implementation of TIRs .
Article 50
Upon request , the Contracting Parties shall provide each other with the information necessary for the application of this Convention , in particular on the registration of road vehicles and containers and their design characteristics .
Article 51
The annexes to this Convention are an integral part of the Convention .
CHAPTER VII FINAL PROVISIONS
Article 52
Signature , ratification , adoption , approval and accession
1 . All States that are members of the United Nations or one of its specialized agencies or of the International Atomic Energy Agency or Contracting Parties to the Statute of the International Court of Justice , as well as all other States invited by the General Assembly of the United Nations , may become Contracting Parties to this Convention ( a ) by signing it without reservation of ratification , acceptance or approval ;
b ) depositing an instrument of ratification , acceptance or approval after signing it , subject to ratification , acceptance or approval ; or
c ) by depositing an instrument of accession .
( 2 ) For the States referred to in paragraph 1 , this Convention shall be with the United Nations Office in Geneva from 1 January 1976 to 31 January 1976 inclusive .
December 1976 for signature , after which it is up to them to accede .
3 . Pursuant to paragraphs 1 and 2 , customs and economic unions may also become Contracting Parties at the same time as all their Member States or at any time after all their Member States have become Contracting Parties to this Convention .
However , these unions do not have the right to vote .
4 . Instruments of ratification , acceptance , approval or accession shall be deposited with the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations .


1 . This Convention shall enter into force six months after the date on which five of the States referred to in Article 52 , paragraph 1 , have signed it , or deposited their instruments of ratification , acceptance , approval or accession , without reservation .
2 . After five of the States referred to in Article 52 , paragraph 1 , have signed or deposited their instruments of ratification , acceptance , approval or accession , the Convention shall enter into force for all new Contracting Parties six months after the date on which they deposited their instruments of ratification , acceptance , approval or accession .
( 3 ) Any instrument of ratification , acceptance , approval or accession deposited after the entry into force of an amendment to this Convention shall be deemed to have been deposited for this Convention as amended .
( 4 ) Any instrument of this kind deposited after acceptance of an amendment but before its entry into force shall be deemed to have been deposited on the date of entry into force of the amendment to this Convention , as amended .


1 . Any Contracting Party may denounce this Convention by notification to the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations .
2 . Denunciation shall take effect fifteen months after receipt of the notification by the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations .
( 3 ) The validity of TIR carnets accepted by a customs outlet prior to the date on which the denunciation takes effect shall not be affected by the denunciation ; likewise , the liability of the guarantor associations under the terms of this Convention shall remain in force .


If the number of States Parties is less than five after the entry into force of this Convention for twelve consecutive months , this Convention shall cease to apply at the end of this twelve @-@ month period .

Termination of the 1959 TIR- Convention
( 1 ) This Convention shall , upon entry into force , repeal and replace the TIR- Convention of 1859 in relations between the Contracting Parties .
( 2 ) Certificates of registration issued for road vehicles and containers under the terms of the 1959 TIR Convention shall be recognised by the Contracting Parties to this Convention for the carriage of goods under customs lock and key during their period of validity or subject to renewal , provided that the vehicles and containers continue to comply with the conditions under which they were originally registered .

Dispute resolution
( 1 ) Disputes between two or more Contracting Parties concerning the interpretation or application of this Convention shall , if possible , be settled by negotiation between them or by other means .
( 2 ) Disputes between two or more Contracting Parties concerning the interpretation or application of this Convention which cannot be resolved in the manner provided for in paragraph 1 shall be referred , at the request of one of them , to an arbitral tribunal composed as follows : Each of the parties to the dispute shall appoint an arbitrator ; the two arbitrators shall appoint another arbitrator as chairman of the arbitral tribunal .
If , three months after receipt of the request , one of the parties has not yet appointed an arbitrator , or if the arbitrators have not yet elected a chairman , each of the parties may request the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations to appoint an arbitrator or the chairman of the arbitration tribunal .
( 3 ) The decision of the arbitral tribunal formed in accordance with subsection 2 shall be binding on the parties to the dispute .
( 4 ) The arbitral tribunal shall adopt its own rules of procedure .
( 5 ) The arbitral tribunal shall decide by majority vote .
( 6 ) Any dispute which should arise between the parties to the dispute as a result of the interpretation and conduct of the award may be referred by one of the parties to the arbitral tribunal which rendered the award for a decision .
Article 58

( 1 ) Any State may , when signing or ratifying this Convention or acceding to it , declare that it does not feel bound by Article 57 , paragraphs 2 to 6 .
The other contracting parties shall not be bound by these paragraphs with respect to any contracting party making such a reservation .
( 2 ) Any Contracting Party making a reservation under paragraph 1 may at any time withdraw it by notification to the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations .
( 3 ) Except for the reservations provided for in paragraph 1 , no reservation shall be permitted with regard to this Convention .

Procedure for amending this Convention
( 1 ) This Convention and its annexes may be amended on a proposal from a Contracting Party in accordance with the procedure provided for in this Article .
( 2 ) Any proposal to amend this Convention shall be examined by a Management Committee composed of all the Contracting Parties in accordance with the Rules of Procedure set out in Annex 8 .
Any such amendment , examined or elaborated at the meeting of the Management Committee and adopted by the Committee by a two @-@ thirds majority of its members present and voting , shall be notified to the Contracting Parties by the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations for adoption .
3 . Subject to Article 60 , any proposed amendment notified in accordance with paragraph 2 shall enter into force for all Contracting Parties three months after the expiry of a period of twelve months from the date of notification , if during that period no State that is a Contracting Party has notified the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations of an objection to the proposed amendment .
4 . Where an objection to a proposal for amendment has been notified pursuant to paragraph 3 , the amendment shall be deemed not to have been accepted and shall have no effect whatsoever .
Article 60
Special procedures for amending Annexes 1 , 2 , 3 , 4 , 5 , 6 and 7
1 . Any proposal to amend Annexes 1 , 2 , 3 , 4 , 5 , 6 and 7 examined in accordance with Article 59 ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) shall enter into force on the date set by the Management Committee upon adoption of the proposal , unless , at an earlier date set by the Management Committee on the same occasion , one fifth of the States which are Contracting Parties or five of those States , whichever is less , notify the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations of their objections to the amendment .
The data referred to in this paragraph shall be determined by the Management Committee by a two @-@ thirds majority of its members present and voting .
( 2 ) The amendment adopted in accordance with paragraph 1 shall , when it enters into force , supersede all previous provisions to which it relates for all Contracting Parties .
Article 61
Requests , communications and observations
The Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations shall inform all Contracting Parties and all States referred to in Article 52 , paragraph 1 , of all requests , notifications and objections arising from Articles 59 and 60 and of the date of entry into force of any amendment .

Revision conference
1 . A State which is a Contracting Party may , by notification to the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations , request the convening of a conference for the revision of this Convention .
2 . A Review Conference to which all the Contracting Parties and all States referred to in Article 52 , paragraph 1 , shall be convened by the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations if , within six months of the date on which the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations has made the notification , at least one quarter of the States which are Contracting Parties inform him of their agreement to the request .
3 . A Review Conference to which all the Contracting Parties and all States referred to in Article 52 , paragraph 1 , shall be convened by the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations even if the Management Committee has notified a request to that effect .
The Management Committee shall decide by a majority of its members present and voting whether such a request should be addressed to the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations .
4 . Where a Conference is convened in accordance with paragraph 1 or 3 , the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations shall inform all Parties accordingly and invite them to submit within three months the proposals to be examined at the Conference .
The Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations shall forward the provisional agenda and the text of these proposals to all Parties at least three months before the start of the Conference .
Article 63
Notifications
In addition to the notifications and communications referred to in Articles 61 and 62 , the Secretary @-@ General of the United Nations shall notify all States referred to in Article 52 ( a ) of the signatures , ratifications , acceptances , approvals and accessions referred to in Article 52 ;
b ) the dates of entry into force of this Convention in accordance with Article 53 ;
( c ) denunciations under Article 54 ;
( d ) the expiry of this Convention in accordance with Article 55 ;
( e ) reservations under Article 58 .

