The objective of this Agreement between the Community and Egypt is to promote global cooperation between the Parties in order to contribute to Egypt &apos;s economic and social development and to facilitate the deepening of their relations .
To this end , provisions and measures in the field of economic , technical and financial cooperation and trade will be defined and implemented .
TITLE I ECONOMIC , TECHNICAL AND FINANCIAL COOPERATION

The Community and Egypt are establishing cooperation with a view to contributing to the development of that country through measures complementing Egypt &apos;s own efforts and to strengthening existing economic relations on the broadest possible basis and for the benefit of both parties .

In implementing the cooperation referred to in Article 2 , particular account will be taken of : - the objectives and priorities of Egypt &apos;s development plans and programmes ,
- the appropriateness of implementing integrated actions through the concerted use of various measures ,
- the expediency of supporting regional cooperation between Egypt and other states .

( 1 ) The purpose of Community @-@ Egypt cooperation is to promote , in particular , the following objectives : - Community participation in Egypt &apos;s efforts to develop production and economic infrastructure with a view to diversifying the structure of its economy .
This participation will take place in particular in the context of the industrialisation of Egypt and the modernisation of its agriculture ;
- marketing and promotion of goods exported by Egypt ;
- industrial cooperation with a view to developing Egypt &apos;s industrial production , in particular through appropriate measures , to encourage Community participation in the implementation of Egypt &apos;s industrial development programmes ;
- encourage the organisation of contacts and meetings between Egyptian and Community industrial policy leaders , investors and enterprises in order to support the establishment of new industrial relations , in accordance with the objectives of the Agreement ;
- facilitate the acquisition of patents and other industrial property on favourable terms through financing under Protocol 1 or through appropriate other arrangements with undertakings and bodies within the Community ;
- to enable the removal of the extra @-@ tariff or non @-@ quota barriers to access to the relevant markets ;
- cooperation in the field of science , technology and environmental protection ;
- the participation of Community undertakings in the research , production and processing programmes aimed at exploiting Egypt &apos;s resources and in all activities aimed at exploiting those resources on the ground , as well as the proper implementation of cooperation and investment contracts concluded for this purpose between the respective undertakings ;
- cooperation in the fisheries sector ;
- the promotion of private investment in the interests of both parties ;
- mutual information on the economic and financial situation and developments to the extent necessary for the proper functioning of the Agreement .
2 . The Parties may define other areas for cooperation .
Article 5
1 . In order to achieve the objectives of the Agreement , the Cooperation Council shall define the general approach of cooperation at regular intervals .
2 . It shall be the task of the Cooperation Council to seek ways and means of facilitating the implementation of cooperation in the areas defined in Article 4 .
To this end , it may take decisions .

The Community will contribute to the financing of measures likely to promote the development of Egypt under the conditions set out in Protocol 1 on technical and financial cooperation , taking into account the possibilities for triangular cooperation .

The Parties shall facilitate the proper implementation of cooperation and investment treaties which are in the interests of both parties and fall within the framework of the Agreement .
