Priority must be given to those measures which have the least impact on the functioning of the Agreement .
The scope of these measures must be limited to what is strictly necessary to remedy the difficulties encountered .
The safeguard measures will be notified immediately to the Cooperation Council and will be the subject of regular consultations , in particular with a view to their abolition as soon as possible .
3 . For the implementation of paragraph 2 , the following shall apply : ( a ) With regard to Articles 33 and 34 , a consultation shall take place in the Cooperation Council before appropriate action is taken by the Contracting Party concerned .
( b ) If exceptional circumstances necessitating immediate intervention preclude prior examination , the Contracting Party concerned may , in the cases referred to in Articles 33 and 34 , immediately take the necessary precautionary measures to remedy the situation .
Article 36
The Contracting Party concerned may take the necessary safeguard measures in the event of balance of payments difficulties which have already occurred or are seriously threatened by one or more Member States of the Community or Egypt .
Priority must be given to those measures which have the least impact on the functioning of the Agreement .
They shall be communicated without delay to the other Contracting Party and shall be the subject of regular consultations in the Cooperation Council , in particular with a view to their abolition as soon as possible .
