Article 38
1 . The Cooperation Council shall consist of representatives of the Community and its Member States , on the one hand , and representatives of Egypt , on the other .
2 . The Cooperation Council shall express its views by mutual agreement between the Community , on the one hand , and Egypt , on the other .
Article 39
1 . The Cooperation Council shall be chaired alternately by one of the Contracting Parties in accordance with the details to be laid down in its rules of procedure .
2 . The Cooperation Council shall meet once a year at the instigation of its President .
It shall also meet at the request of a Contracting Party in accordance with its Rules of Procedure , as often as this is necessary due to special circumstances .
Article 40
1 . The Cooperation Council may decide to set up committees to assist it in the performance of its tasks .
2 . The Cooperation Council shall lay down in its rules of procedure the composition , tasks and functioning of these committees .
Article 41
The Cooperation Council shall take all appropriate measures to facilitate the necessary cooperation and contact between the European Parliament and the representatives of the Egyptian People &apos;s Assembly .
Article 42
Each Contracting Party shall , at the request of the other Contracting Party , communicate all relevant information on the agreements concluded by it , insofar as they include customs tariff or trade provisions , and on changes to its customs tariff or foreign trade regime .
Should these amendments or agreements have a direct and particular impact on the functioning of the Agreement , consultations shall be held in the Cooperation Council at the request of the other Party in order to take account of the interests of the Parties .
Article 43
1 . The Contracting Parties shall take all appropriate measures , of a general or special nature , to fulfil their obligations under this Agreement .
They shall ensure the implementation of the objectives laid down in this Agreement .
2 . If one Party considers that the other Party has not fulfilled an obligation under the Convention , it may take appropriate measures .
It shall first provide the Cooperation Council with all the information necessary for a thorough examination of the situation with a view to finding a solution acceptable to the Parties .
Priority must be given to those measures which have the least impact on the functioning of the Agreement .
These measures shall be communicated to the Cooperation Council without delay and may be the subject of consultations within the Cooperation Council at the request of the other Contracting Party .

This Agreement shall in no way preclude any Party from taking any measures ( a ) it deems necessary to prevent disclosure of information contrary to its essential security interests ;
( b ) concerning trade in arms , munitions , war material or research , development or production indispensable for defence purposes , provided that such measures do not adversely affect conditions of competition for products not intended specifically for military purposes ;
( c ) which it considers essential for its own security in times of war or in the event of serious international tensions .
Article 45
- in the areas covered by this Agreement , the regime applied by Egypt vis @-@ à @-@ vis the Community must not lead to different treatment between Member States , their nationals or their companies ;
- the Community rules applicable to Egypt must not lead to different treatment of Egyptian nationals or companies .
Article 46
In accordance with the procedure for the negotiation of the Agreement , the Parties shall examine , for the first time from the beginning of 1979 and later from the beginning of 1984 , the results of the Agreement as well as any improvements which can be made by both sides from 1 January 1980 and from 1 January 1985 on the basis of the experience gained by that date in the functioning of the Agreement and the objectives of the Agreement .
Article 47
Protocols 1 and 2 and Annexes A , B , C and D form part of the Agreement .
The declarations and exchanges of letters are contained in the Final Act , which forms part of the Agreement .
Article 48
Any Contracting Party may terminate this Agreement by notifying the other Contracting Party .
This Agreement shall expire twelve months after the date of notification .

This Agreement shall apply to the territories in which the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community is applicable in accordance with that Treaty and to the territory of the Arab Republic of Egypt .
Article 50
This Agreement is drawn up in two original texts in Danish , English , French , German , Italian , Dutch and Arabic , each text being equally authentic .
Article 51
This Agreement shall be subject to the consent of the Parties in accordance with their own procedures .
This Agreement shall enter into force on the first day of the second month following the date on which the Contracting Parties notified each other of the conclusion of the procedures referred to in paragraph 1 .
The Agreement between the European Economic Community and the Arab Republic of Egypt of 18 December 1972 expires on the same day .
