between the European Economic Community ( EEC ) and its Member States , Belgium , Denmark , the Federal Republic of Germany , France , Ireland , Italy , Luxembourg , the Netherlands , the United Kingdom ( Member States ) , of the one part , and the International Development Organisation ( Organisation ) , of the other part
CONSIDERING NEIGHBOURS - ( a ) The EEC has decided to contribute to the Special Programme of Action established at the Conference on International Economic Cooperation in order to help meet the immediate needs of individual low @-@ income countries whose development is hampered by general resource transfer problems .
( b ) The EEC has requested the Organisation to administer for it , in order to implement this Decision , a special account ( Special Action Account ) for the equivalent of a total of USD 385 million , kept separately from all other accounts and assets of the Organisation and to be used for loans ( Special Action Loans ) , which will be added to the amount of the programme envisaged by the Organisation , both under programmes and for projects during the commitment period of the Special Action Account for each country to which they may be granted , on the basis set out below .
( c ) The aim of the EEC and the Member States is to have all the contribution made by the Member States committed within six months of the entry into force of the Agreement and , as far as possible , disbursed in the form of loans within two years of its entry into force , and the Organisation will do its utmost to achieve this objective .
( d ) The EEC and the Organisation have consulted each other on the proposed implementation and management of this Agreement and on commitments with a view to ensuring a broad and balanced geographical distribution within the framework of this Agreement .
To this end , the EEC Organisation has presented a table indicating how it intends to apply the criteria laid down in this Agreement ,
HAVE AGREED THE PARTIES FOLLOWING :
ARTICLE I
Setting up and managing the Special Action Account

The Organisation shall set up a special account called a &quot; Special Action Account &quot; consisting of the funds which the Member States contribute to the Special Action Account pursuant to this Convention , which shall be held and used in trust by the Organisation as Administrator ( in this capacity the Organisation shall be referred to as the &quot; Administrator &quot; ) for the sole purpose specified in this Agreement and in accordance with the provisions of this Agreement .
The Special Action Account is held separately and separately from all other accounts and assets of the organization .

Each Member State shall , as a contribution to the Special Action Account , pay in its national currency an amount corresponding to the amount in US dollars indicated below for that Member State at the time of signature of this Agreement . Member States * Amount ( in millions of US dollars ) * Belgium * 15.90 * Denmark * 11.28 * Federal Republic of Germany * 119.08 * France * 56.48 * Ireland * 1.04 * Italy * 34.92 * Luxembourg * 0.50 * Netherlands * 30.80 * United Kingdom * 115.00 * 385.00 . *

Contributions shall be paid as follows : a ) Payment shall be made in the form of cash or non @-@ interest @-@ bearing notes of the Member State , payable on request in the currency of the State concerned to the Organisation acting as manager of the Special Action Account and deposited with the depositary institution of the Organisation in the country concerned .
( b ) Payment shall be made in two instalments , i ) the first in the amount of at least 45 % of the contribution within 30 days of the entry into force of this Agreement or at any other time agreed between the EEC and the administrator ;
( ii ) the second in the amount of the remainder of the contribution to 1 January 1979 or at any other time agreed between the EEC and the administrator , taking into account the deadlines for parliamentary approval of the annual budgets .
( c ) Any Member State may , if desired , make payments before the above dates .

The administrator , in accordance with the usual procedures of the Organization , makes approximately proportional drawings on the cash or promissory notes in order to cover the expenditure on the Special Action Loans and adequately compensate the Special Action Account .
ARTICLE II
Use of the Special Promotional Account

All amounts credited to the Special Action Account will be used exclusively by the administrator , in accordance with the provisions of the EEC , to grant Special Action Loans to member countries of the Organisation with low income and intangible needs , in particular the least developed ( 1 ) and most disadvantaged ( 1 ) developing countries whose development prospects have been substantially reduced by external factors that are facing general resource transfer problems and may have debt service difficulties as a result .
In granting these loans , in accordance with the conditions of the EEC , the administrator shall be guided by the following factors :
( i ) the relative poverty of the developing country concerned and its long @-@ term growth potential ;
( iii ) the extent to which international economic factors have contributed to the country &apos;s current and foreseeable economic problems ;
( iv ) the development and future prospects of the country &apos;s export earnings ;
( v ) the country &apos;s capacity to ensure imports of goods essential to the development process ;
( vi ) the composition and tendency of the country &apos;s debt service and its further borrowing capacity to borrow on unfavourable terms ; and
( vii ) the extent to which the problems of the countries concerned can be resolved by contributions from other sources .

Each Special Action Loan is intended to finance a clearly defined and rapidly disbursable development programme or project ( including a sectoral project ) assessed , approved and managed , whether or not part of the Organisation &apos;s lending programme , in accordance with the procedures and practices applicable to development credits financed from the Organisation &apos;s ordinary resources , taking into account the objective of additionality referred to in point ( b ) of the preamble to this Agreement .
The funds of the Special Action Account may not be used in place of ordinary funds of the International Bank for Reconstruction and Development ( Bank ) or the Organisation , which are bound by a loan or credit for a programme or project already approved by the Directors of the Bank or the Organisation on the date of entry into force of this Agreement .

With the exception of Section 4 , Special Action Loans are subject to the same repayment terms as those applicable to development loans generally granted by the Organisation and are therefore repayable in 50 years for ten free years .
Special action loans are not subject to interest .

Special action loans are granted in one or more Member States &apos; currencies and are repayable in those currencies .
Section 5
The administrator shall be entitled , in accordance with the usual procedures of the Organisation , to charge each beneficiary of a Special Action Loan , for the remuneration of the services provided by it under this Agreement , an annual administration fee of three quarters of one per cent ( 3 / 4 of one per cent ) of the amount of the loan capital not yet repaid at that time , in a currency acceptable to the Organisation .
Amounts for the payment of this fee are to be paid directly to the organisation which withholds them .

Each Special Action Loan must be identified by a separate loan agreement between the beneficiary country and the administrator , specifying in particular the origin of the funds .

The proceeds from each Special Action Loan may be used for expenditure in the currency of the recipient country or for goods or services produced or provided in a Member State ; ii ) in developing countries which are members of the Organisation and which may be the recipients of a Special Action Loan in accordance with what the administrator has determined at the time of granting the loan .

Capital repayments of Special Action Loans shall be made into the Special Action Account and the amount thereby repaid in the currency of a Member State shall be transferred back to the Member State concerned by the administrator as soon as possible after receipt of the Special Action Loans .
The organization is not liable for defaults in the repayment of special action loans .
ARTICLE III
Reports ; consultations

The administrator shall inform the EEC of the projects and programmes being prepared for examination by the Directors and approved by the Directors until all the Special Action Loans have been granted in full .
During the disbursement of the Special Action Loans , the administrator shall inform the EEC on a quarterly basis of the development of the Special Action Loans and the expenditure incurred for this purpose .
The administrator shall send to the EEC , as soon as possible after the end of the financial year , a detailed account of the Special Action Account with an opinion of the Organisation &apos;s external auditors on this account .
After full disbursement of the Special Action Loans , the administrator of the EEC shall submit as soon as possible a detailed report on the projects and programmes financed by the Special Action Account .

The administrator shall draw up and maintain appropriate records and accounts showing the contributions to the Special Action Account , the obligations to be financed from the funds in the account , the amounts received and paid out of the account and the repayments to the Member States .

The EEC and the administrators shall cooperate closely to achieve the objectives of this Agreement .
To this end , the EEC ( represented by the Commission of the European Communities ) and the administrators shall from time to time hold an exchange of views on the status of the Special Action Account , the progress of programmes or projects financed by Special Action Accounts and any other issues relating to the provisions of this Agreement , pending the full disbursement of the funds of the Special Action Account .
ARTICLE IV
Termination ; Distribution

If this Agreement does not enter into force on 31 December 1978 or at a later date , as may be agreed by the EEC and the Organisation , the Agreement and all obligations of the parties arising therefrom shall lapse with immediate effect .

Once the total principal amount of all Special Action Loans drawn on by the beneficiaries has been repaid and transferred back to the Member States in accordance with Article II ( 8 ) of this Agreement , this Agreement and all obligations of the parties arising therefrom shall be terminated with immediate effect .
ARTICLE V
Final Provisions

This Agreement shall be subject to approval by each Member State and the EEC in accordance with the procedural provisions of each Party .

The Governments of the Member States shall notify the General Secretariat of the Council of the European Communities of the completion of the procedures concerning them .
The General Secretariat shall forward these notifications to the Organisation together with a notification of the proper approval of this Agreement by the EEC .

This Agreement shall take effect and shall enter into force on the first day of the month following the date of receipt by the Organisation of the aforementioned notifications .

