between the European Atomic Energy Community and the Swiss Confederation in the field of controlled nuclear fusion and plasma physics
THE EUROPEAN ATOMIC COMMUNITY , hereinafter referred to as &quot; Euratom , &quot; represented by the Commission of the European Communities , hereinafter referred to as &quot; Commission , &quot;
AND THE SWITZERLAND EIDGENOSSENSHIP , hereinafter referred to as &quot; Switzerland , &quot; represented by the Swiss Federal Council , hereinafter referred to as &quot; Bundesrat , &quot;
CONSIDERING REASONS : Euratom has been implementing multiannual programmes of research and training in this field since 1959 under a long @-@ term joint programme covering all activities in the field of controlled nuclear fusion and plasma physics at Euratom ; these programmes are intended to lead to the industrial production and marketing of controlled fusion reactors and are implemented inter alia through association contracts and an agreement on the promotion of staff exchanges , the last of which is the fourth five @-@ year programme covering the period 1976 @-@ 1980 .
This programme involves the construction of a large experimental facility , the JET ( Joint European Torus ) project , the construction and operation of which will be entrusted to a Chapter V Joint Undertaking of the Euratom Treaty , hereinafter referred to as the JET Joint Undertaking .
Switzerland has been involved in controlled nuclear fusion and plasma physics research for several years and is very familiar with the area in question .
Given that a great deal of work remains to be done before controlled fusion can be put to practical use , it is in the interest of the Parties to this Agreement to pool their efforts in this area in order to avoid unnecessary duplication and to speed up their respective research activities , which have been given a higher priority by the energy crisis ;
HOW TO CONVENT :
A. Subject of the Agreement

The aim of this agreement is to enable each Contracting Party , by pooling its research efforts in the field of controlled fusion and plasma physics , to derive maximum benefit from the resources allocated to mutual research , to avoid unnecessary duplication and , accordingly , to achieve more quickly the common objective of this research , i.e. the cost @-@ competitive generation of electricity through the use of the controlled fusion reaction .


In order to achieve the objective of this Agreement , the Parties shall associate their respective research programmes defined in Annexes I and II to this Agreement , hereinafter referred to as the &quot; Euratom Programme &quot; and the &quot; Swiss Programme . &quot;
In order to ensure effective cooperation , the Swiss programme adopts the long @-@ term objectives and forms of cooperation of the Euratom programme and , after examination by the institutions referred to in Articles 5 to 10 and Article 16 of this Agreement , will be extended or amended to include , where appropriate , new activities relevant to the Euratom programme .
Each time the Parties adopt a new programme , it replaces the programme ( s ) listed in Annex I and II to this Agreement .
The association provided for in paragraph 1 shall be implemented by : - appropriate participation of each of the Contracting Parties during the preparation and implementation of the programmes of the other Party ;
- the exchange of personnel between the laboratories concerned in the Euratom Member States , Switzerland and third countries with which Euratom has concluded an agreement similar to the present one , hereinafter referred to as &quot; associated third countries , &quot; as well as the laboratories participating in the Euratom programme ;
- reciprocal financing of programmes ;
- mutual right of access to the scientific and technical results of the respective programmes .

Within the framework of the objective of the present agreement , Switzerland is participating in the JET project .
B. Legal instruments to achieve the objective of the Agreement


In order to implement the association provided for in Article 2 ( 1 ) of this Agreement , the Parties shall conclude an Association Treaty , hereinafter referred to as the &quot; Association Treaty , &quot; which shall as far as possible correspond to those concluded between the Commission and the States and undertakings or persons , hereinafter referred to as the &quot; Associated Institutions , &quot; with a view to the implementation of the Euratom programme .
With the same objective in mind , Euratom shall ensure that , on the date of entry into force of this Agreement , Switzerland participates in the Agreement on the promotion of staff exchanges concluded between the Commission and the associated institutions , hereinafter referred to as the &quot; Agreement on the Exchange of Personnel . &quot;

With regard to participation in the JET project , Switzerland will be a member of the JET Joint Undertaking on the date of entry into force of this Agreement , the Statute of which it accepts .

Furthermore , Euratom shall ensure that Switzerland may become a contracting party to any treaty whose objective falls within the scope of this Agreement , with the exception of association agreements or other similar agreements concluded by Euratom during the period of validity of this Agreement .
C. Institutions to achieve the objective of the Agreement


The institutions responsible for implementing the Association referred to in Article 2 ( 1 ) of this Agreement are described in Articles 5 to 10 of this Agreement and in the Association Treaty .

The organs of the JET Joint Undertaking are described in the Articles of Association of the JET Joint Undertaking .
Article 5
The Association Agreement provides in particular for the establishment of a Steering Committee composed of competent representatives of the Commission and the Bundesrat .
This Steering Committee will be responsible for : - implementing the Association Treaty ;
- define the details of the programmes covered by the Treaty ;
- monitor and steer the development of research in order to achieve the best possible results in accordance with the objectives of this Agreement .


Switzerland will be represented by a maximum of two delegates to the Liaison Group established under the Euratom programme , hereinafter referred to as the &quot; VG . &quot;
The VG , which is responsible for the exchange of information and cooperation on all issues relating to the current or planned programmes and activities in the field of the Euratom programme , shall carry out this task in respect of all research and development activities to which this Agreement relates .
In particular , it promotes cooperation and coordination between the associated institutions and aligns its activities , in the interest of both Parties , with the common objective set out in the Euratom and Swiss programmes and in Article 1 of this Agreement , taking due account of scientific and technological developments in the world .

In accordance with its Rules of Procedure , the VG appoints one or more Swiss representatives to the Advisory Groups established under the Euratom programme whenever requested by the competent Swiss authorities .
The Advisory Groups which submit research proposals to the VG with a view to ensuring that the funds allocated to the Euratom programme produce the best possible scientific results will carry out this task in respect of all the research and development work referred to in this Agreement .


Switzerland is represented on the Committee of Directors set up under the Euratom programme by the Director of one of the laboratories involved .
The Committee of Directors , which is responsible for monitoring the implementation of the Euratom programme and making the best use of the capacities of the laboratories involved in the work carried out under the programme , will carry out this task in respect of all research and development work covered by this Agreement .
In particular , it ensures the best possible use of staff and the exchange of staff between the laboratories involved in the implementation of the Euratom programme and the Swiss programme .

A Swiss representative is entitled to attend meetings of all the coordination committees set up under the Euratom programme .
The Coordination Committees , which make appropriate proposals to the Committee of Directors on how best to make use of the resources , staff and knowledge and capabilities of the laboratories involved in the implementation of the Euratom programme in their respective fields , shall carry out this task in respect of all research and development activities covered by this Agreement .
Article 8
Switzerland is represented on the Merger Advisory Committee , hereinafter referred to as the BAF .
The BAF comprises a representative of each Euratom Member State , Switzerland and any associated third country responsible for nuclear and energy research .
At the request of the Commission , BAF will advise the Commission on the implementation of the programme and any changes in its orientations , as well as on the preparation of future programmes and the definition of their overall scope , the coordination and integration of national merger activities at Community level .

The opinions of the BAF , the VG , the Committee of Directors , the Advisory Groups and the Coordination Committees are of an advisory nature .
The VG &apos;s opinion on urgent action is compulsory , as is the opinion of the Committee of Directors on personnel exchanges .

The representatives of the two Parties shall participate in the work of all technical advisory bodies or administrative bodies established for the purposes of this Agreement .
D . Financial and fiscal provisions of the agreement
Article 11

Switzerland &apos;s financial contribution to the Euratom programme in accordance with this Agreement shall be fixed annually at an amount proportionate to the Euratom share of the costs of the Euratom programme as the gross domestic product of Switzerland was to the total gross domestic product of Euratom and Switzerland the year before last .
Concerning the JET project , this financial contribution relates to Euratom &apos;s participation in the Joint Undertaking once it is established .
In addition , Switzerland will transfer to the JET Joint Undertaking an amount to be determined in accordance with the financial provisions of the Statute of that Joint Undertaking .

The financial contribution made by Euratom to the financing of work under the Association Treaty and the Agreement on the Exchange of Personnel will be calculated on the same basis as is normally used to calculate Euratom contributions to the financing of work carried out under the relevant Treaties .

The Commission shall inform the Federal Council at the beginning of each year of the amount intended to cover expenditure under the Euratom programme for the year in question .
The Federal Council shall pay the amount due to the Commission pursuant to this Article as follows : 7 / 12 before 15 January and 5 / 12 before 15 January .
The other payment arrangements for the financial contributions of Switzerland and Euratom referred to in this Article are set out in Annex III to this Agreement .
Article 12

Switzerland shall take all necessary measures to exempt Euratom from customs duties or other charges and from import bans and restrictions on the part of goods financed by Euratom intended to be used in Switzerland for activities under this Agreement .

Items imported into Switzerland or purchased there may not be sold in that country for a fee or free of charge , unless subject to conditions approved by the Federal Council .

Commission officials within the meaning of Article 1 of the status of officials of the European Communities whose salaries , salaries and emoluments paid by the Communities are subject to Community tax and who carry out activities covered by this Convention in Switzerland , as well as Swiss persons subject to the aforementioned Staff Regulations and who take part in such activities within the territory of the Euratom Member States , shall be exempt from national taxes on salaries and salaries .
These exemptions do not apply to pensions and annuities paid to such persons .
E. Provisions of the Agreement on access to knowledge
Article 13

The provisions on access to knowledge applicable to the association provided for in Article 2 ( 1 ) of this Agreement are laid down in Articles 14 and 15 of this Agreement , in the Association Agreement and in the Agreement on the Exchange of Personnel .

The provisions on access to knowledge applicable to Switzerland &apos;s participation in the JET Joint Undertaking are laid down in Article 14 of this Agreement and in the Statute of the Joint Undertaking .
Article 14

The right of each Contracting Party to access the knowledge of the other Party is an essential part of this Agreement .

This right is guaranteed by : - rules on the dissemination of knowledge and patents ;
- the exchange of personnel between the participating laboratories in Euratom , Switzerland and associated third countries ;
- taking due account of undertakings in Euratom , Switzerland and associated third countries in the award of contracts for the implementation of the two associated programmes , in accordance with the principle of making the best use of the amounts invested .
Article 15

Knowledge gained during the period of validity of this Agreement in Euratom and in the associated institutions in the field of controlled nuclear fusion and plasma physics shall be communicated to Switzerland and to persons or undertakings conducting research or production activities in Switzerland justifying access to such knowledge under the same conditions as to the Member States , persons or undertakings of Euratom .

The knowledge gained from the research carried out in Switzerland under this Agreement shall be communicated to the Member States of Euratom and associated third countries and to persons or undertakings engaged in research or production activities in a Member State of Euratom or an associated third country justifying access to such knowledge .
The Contracting Parties shall communicate this knowledge to other States , persons or undertakings only if an agreement has been concluded between the Parties to this effect , unless such persons or undertakings carry out research or production activities in Switzerland which justify access to such knowledge .

Where the knowledge referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 of this Article is protected by patents , those patents may be used by the Member States of Euratom , Switzerland , the associated third countries and the persons or undertakings established in the countries concerned for research purposes in pursuit of the objectives of this Agreement .
Member States of Euratom , Switzerland , associated third countries and persons or undertakings established in the countries concerned may be granted , on reasonable terms , licences or sub @-@ licences to use these patents for industrial or commercial purposes , provided that the parties are authorised to grant such licences or sub @-@ licences .

Knowledge arising from the activities of Euratom , the associated institutions and Switzerland prior to the entry into force of this Agreement shall be made available to those States , persons or undertakings to which the knowledge referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 may be communicated , to the extent necessary for the use of the knowledge referred to in these paragraphs .
Patents resulting from the activities referred to in this paragraph shall be made available to any State , person or entity that may obtain a license or sub @-@ license to the patents referred to in paragraph 3 of this Article , to the extent necessary for the use of such licenses or sub @-@ licenses .

This Article shall not affect the rights to which inventors or their successors in title are entitled under their respective national laws .

The Contracting Parties shall refrain from any action which could prejudice the patentability of the inventions arising from the activities referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 of this Article .
F. General and Final Provisions of the Agreement
Article 16

A joint committee will be set up called the Euratom / Switzerland Merger Committee , composed of representatives of the Commission and the Federal Council .

The Euratom / Switzerland Fusion Committee is responsible for the proper implementation of the Agreement .
It shall examine all measures to improve cooperation under the Agreement and shall keep abreast of the state of play .

If one Contracting Party considers that the other Contracting Party has failed to fulfil an obligation under this Agreement , it shall inform the Euratom Switzerland Merger Committee thereof without delay .

The Euratom / Switzerland Fusion Committee may , in order to carry out its tasks , make recommendations on the basis of the opinion of the VG , which will be communicated to the competent authorities of the Euratom countries and Switzerland for the adoption of programmes and budgets in the research areas covered by this agreement .

The Euratom / Switzerland Merger Committee has its own rules of procedure .
The Contracting Parties shall hold the Presidency alternately in accordance with the Rules of Procedure of the Euratom / Switzerland Merger Committee .

The Euratom / Switzerland Fusion Committee meets at the request of one of the Contracting Parties , but at least once a year .
Article 17

Disputes relating to the interpretation or application of this Agreement shall be referred to an arbitration tribunal at the request of either Contracting Party .

The arbitral tribunal referred to in paragraph 1 of this Article shall be established on a case @-@ by @-@ case basis .
It consists of three members .
Each Contracting Party shall appoint a member , and these two members shall appoint a third member to preside over the arbitral tribunal .
If one of the Contracting Parties has not appointed a member within two months of the date on which referral to an arbitral tribunal has been requested in a dispute , or if the two members of the tribunal have not agreed on the appointment of the third member within one month of the election of the second member of the arbitral tribunal , the President of the International Court shall be requested by the Contracting Party or the Contracting Parties to appoint the member concerned .

The proceedings of the arbitral tribunal shall be governed by the arbitral tribunal itself .
The arbitral tribunal shall act by majority vote .
His decisions are binding .

Each Contracting Party shall bear the costs of its own member in the arbitration proceedings ; the costs of the Presidency and the other costs shall be borne equally by both Contracting Parties .
Article 18
The annexes to this Agreement are part of the Agreement .
Article 19

This Agreement will be approved by the Parties in accordance with their own procedures .
It shall enter into force when the parties have informed each other that the necessary procedure has been followed .

This Agreement shall be concluded for the duration of the Euratom programme referred to in Article 1 ; it shall be tacitly renewed in accordance with other relevant Euratom programme decisions .
In the event of such a further programme decision , the extension shall apply for the duration of the new programme , which replaces the Euratom programme listed in Annex I. This agreement shall not be terminated if there are merely delays in the adoption of another Euratom programme .
Prior to any decision on the adoption of a new Euratom programme , the Parties shall consult within the framework of the institutions referred to in Articles 5 to 10 and Article 16 of this Agreement .

Any Contracting Party may terminate this Agreement at any time within a period of six months .


