Article III
Information and market surveillance

Participants shall submit to the Council , on a regular basis and in the shortest possible time , the information which will enable it to monitor and assess the overall situation of the world meat market and the situation on the world market for each type of meat .

Participating developing countries will provide the information they have .
In order to enable these countries to improve their data collection systems , participating developed countries , as well as those participating developing countries which are in a position to do so , will examine favourably any request for technical assistance addressed to them .

The information to be provided by the participants in accordance with paragraph 1 , in accordance with the modalities to be established by the Council , shall include information on developments to date and the current situation , as well as an assessment of production prospects ( including developments in the composition of livestock stocks ) , consumption , prices , stocks and trade in Article II products , as well as any other information deemed necessary by the Council , in particular on competing products .
Participants will also provide information on their internal policies and trade measures , including bilateral and plurilateral commitments in the beef sector , and inform as soon as possible of any changes to these policies and measures which could have an impact on international trade in beef and live bovine animals .
The provisions of this paragraph do not oblige participants to disclose confidential information whose disclosure would impede the implementation of laws or otherwise conflict with the public interest or harm the legitimate commercial interests of public or private companies .

The Secretariat of the MOU monitors changes in market conditions , in particular the size of livestock herds , stocks , slaughter and domestic and international prices , in order to detect early any signs of serious imbalances in supply and demand .
The Secretariat shall keep the Council informed of significant developments on world markets and of prospects for production , consumption , exports and imports .

Pursuant to this article , the Council instructs the Secretariat to draw up and keep informed of an inventory of all measures affecting trade in beef and live bovine animals , including all obligations arising from bilateral , plurilateral and multilateral negotiations .
Article IV
Tasks of the International Meat Council and cooperation between the participants in this Convention

The Council shall meet to assess the situation and prospects of supply and demand on the world market ( a ) on the basis of an interpretative analysis of the current situation and likely developments prepared by the Secretariat of the Agreement on the basis of information provided in accordance with Article III , including information on the implementation of internal and trade policies and all other information available ;
( b ) to examine fully the functioning of this Convention ;
( c ) Provide an opportunity for regular consultations on all issues relating to the international beef trade .

If , on the basis of the assessment of the situation of supply and demand on the world market referred to in paragraph 1 ( a ) , or after examining all relevant information in accordance with Article III ( 3 ) , the Council notes that a serious imbalance exists or threatens to arise on the international meat market , it shall endeavour to identify remedies compatible with the principles and rules of GATT , paying particular attention to the situation in developing countries , by means of consensus for consideration by Governments .

Depending on whether the situation referred to in paragraph 2 is considered temporary or more permanent , the measures referred to in paragraph 2 may include short- , medium- and long @-@ term import measures , such as those of exporting countries , which contribute to improving the overall situation of the world market in accordance with the objectives of this agreement , in particular the objective of enlargement , ever @-@ increasing liberalisation and stability of international meat and livestock markets .

When examining the measures proposed in paragraphs 2 and 3 , due account will be taken , where possible and appropriate , of special and more favourable treatment for developing countries .

Participants shall contribute to the fullest extent possible to the achievement of the objectives of this Agreement as set out in Article I. To this end , and in accordance with the principles and provisions of the General Agreement , Participants shall regularly engage in the discussions provided for in Article IV ( 1 ) ( c ) in order to explore ways of achieving the objectives of this Agreement , in particular the objective of further dismantling barriers to world trade in beef and live bovine animals .
These discussions should pave the way for a subsequent examination of possible solutions to trade problems , in accordance with the principles and rules of the GATT , which can be jointly adopted by all parties concerned in a balance of mutual benefits .

Any participant may , inter alia , bring before the Council any question relating to this Convention ( 2 ) for the same purposes referred to in paragraph 2 .
The Council shall meet within a maximum of 15 days , at the request of a participant , to examine any question relating to this Agreement ( 2 ) .
PART II ADMINISTRATION OF THE CONVENTION
Article V

International Meat Council
An International Meat Council will be set up under GATT .
The Council , composed of representatives of all parties to this Convention , shall fulfil the tasks necessary to implement the provisions of this Convention .
The Council has the services of the GATT Secretariat at its disposal .
The Council shall adopt its own rules of procedure and , in particular , lay down the procedures for consultations provided for in Article IV .

Ordinary and special sessions
The Council normally meets at least twice a year .
The Chairman may , however , convene a special meeting of his own accord or at the request of a party to this Convention .


The Council &apos;s decisions are reached by consensus .
A Council decision on a question referred for consideration shall be deemed to have been taken if no member of the Council raises a formal objection to the adoption of a proposal .

Cooperation with other organisations
The Council shall make all appropriate arrangements for consultation and cooperation with intergovernmental and non @-@ governmental organisations .

Admission of observers
( a ) The Council may invite any non @-@ participating country to be represented as an observer at a Council meeting .
( b ) The Council may also invite any organisation referred to in paragraph 4 to attend a meeting as an observer .
PART III FINAL PROVISIONS
Article VI

Assumption ( 3 )
( a ) This Convention shall be open to the Governments of the Members of the United Nations Organization or one of its specialized agencies and of the European Economic Community for adoption by signature or in any other form .
b ) Any government ( 4 ) which accepts this Agreement may , upon acceptance , make a reservation regarding the acceptance of any provision of this Agreement .
This reservation requires the consent of the participants .
( c ) This Agreement shall be deposited with the Director @-@ General of the Parties to the GATT , who shall , within the shortest possible time , transmit to each Participant a certified copy thereof and a notification of each acceptance .
The French , English and Spanish texts of this Convention are equally binding .
d ) Upon entry into force of this Agreement , the International Meat Consultative Group shall be dissolved .

Provisional application
Any Government may deposit with the Director @-@ General of the Parties to the General Agreement a declaration on the provisional application of this Agreement .
Any government depositing such a declaration shall apply this Agreement provisionally and shall be deemed to be a party to this Agreement provisionally .


This Convention shall enter into force for those participants who have accepted it on 1 January 1980 .
Participants who accept this Agreement after that date will be subject to it from the date of their acceptance .

Validity
This agreement will be concluded for a period of three years .
Unless the Council decides otherwise at least eighty days before the end of the respective period of validity , its validity shall be extended for a further three years .


Unless amending provisions are contained elsewhere in this Convention , the Council may recommend amending the provisions of this Convention .
Proposed amendments shall enter into force upon adoption by the governments of all participants .

Relation of the Agreement to the GATT
The provisions of this Agreement do not affect the rights and obligations of GATT participants ( 5 ) .


Any participant may withdraw from this Agreement .
The withdrawal shall take effect at the end of sixty days after receipt of the written notice of resignation by the Director @-@ General of the Contracting Parties to the GATT . ( 1 ) This recital shall apply only between participants who are Contracting Parties to the GATT .
