The International Council for Milk Products established pursuant to Article VII ( 1 ) ( a ) of this Convention - hereinafter referred to as the Council - may decide that this Convention shall also apply to other products containing milk products within the meaning of paragraph 1 if it considers it necessary to achieve the objectives and provisions of this Convention .
Article III


Participants shall submit to the Council , on a regular basis and in the shortest possible time , the information necessary to monitor and assess the overall situation on the world market for milk products and the situation on the world market for each milk product .

Participating developing countries will provide the information they have .
In order to enable these countries to improve their data collection systems , participating developed countries , as well as those participating developing countries which are in a position to do so , will examine favourably any request for technical assistance addressed to them .

The information to be provided by the participants in accordance with paragraph 1 , in accordance with the modalities to be established by the Council , shall include information on developments to date , the current situation and prospects of production , consumption , prices , stocks and trade , including other than normal commercial transactions , for the products of Article II , as well as any other information deemed necessary by the Council .
Participants will also provide information on their internal policies and trade measures , as well as on their bilateral , plurilateral or multilateral commitments in the dairy sector , and will notify as soon as possible any changes to these policies and measures which could have an impact on international trade in dairy products .
The provisions of this paragraph do not oblige participants to disclose confidential information , the disclosure of which would impede the implementation of laws or otherwise prejudice the public interest or the legitimate commercial interests of public or private undertakings .

Pursuant to this article , the Council instructs the Secretariat to draw up and update an inventory of all measures affecting trade in dairy products , including all obligations arising from bilateral , plurilateral and multilateral negotiations .
Article IV
Tasks of the International Council for Milk Products and Cooperation between Participants in this Agreement

The Council shall meet to assess ( a ) the situation and prospects on the world market for dairy products on the basis of a progress report prepared by the Secretariat on the basis of the documents provided by the participants pursuant to Article III , the data relating to the application of the Protocols of Article VI and all other data available to it ;
( b ) Review the functioning of this Convention .

If the Council , having assessed the situation and prospects on the world market in accordance with paragraph 1 ( a ) , notes that a serious market imbalance arises or threatens to arise for milk products as a whole or for one or more particular dairy products which may affect or affect international trade , it shall endeavour to identify possible solutions for consideration by Governments , paying particular attention to the situation in developing countries .

Depending on the Council &apos;s view that the situation referred to in paragraph 2 is temporary or more permanent , the measures referred to in paragraph 2 may include short- , medium- and long @-@ term measures contributing to an improvement in the overall situation of the world market .

Where possible and appropriate , due account should be taken of the special and more favourable treatment to be granted to developing countries when examining the measures that could be taken under paragraphs 2 and 3 .

Any participant may , inter alia , bring before the Council any question relating to this Convention ( 1 ) for the same purposes referred to in paragraph 2 .
Each participant agrees without delay to consultations on all issues relating to this Convention ( 1 ) .
