Article V
Food aid and other than normal commercial operations

Participants ( a ) contribute , in cooperation with FAO and other interested organisations , to better understanding the value of dairy products in improving food standards and the ways in which these products can be made available to developing countries ;
( b ) Provide dairy products to developing countries in the context of food aid , in accordance with the objectives of this Convention , in accordance with their capacities .
Participants should inform the Council each year in advance , as far as possible , of the volume , quantities and destination of the food aid they envisage .
Furthermore , participants should , if possible , inform the Council in advance of any intended changes to the announced programme .
Contributions to food aid may take the form of bilateral actions , joint projects or multilateral programmes , in particular the World Food Programme ;
( c ) Considering the desirability of coordinating their efforts in this field and the need to avoid damaging interference with the normal structure of production , consumption and international trade , hold discussions in the Council on the promised and requested supplies of dairy products under food aid or on preferential terms .

Free exports to developing countries , exports for aid or welfare purposes to developing countries and other transactions other than normal commercial transactions are carried out in accordance with the Principles of Surplus Disposal and Consultative Obligations established by the FAO .
The Council is therefore working closely with the Consultative Subcommittee on Surplus Disposal .

In accordance with the conditions and modalities to be defined by the Council , the Council shall , upon request , discuss and consult all transactions which are not normal commercial transactions and are not covered by the Convention on the Interpretation and Application of Articles VI , XVI and XXIII of the General Agreement on Customs and Trade .
